
[1]philosophize

   PHILOS'OPHIZE, v.i. [from philosophy.] To reason like a philosopher; to
   search into the reason and nature of things; to investigate phenomena
   and assign rational causes for their existence. Sir Isaac Newton lays
   down four rules of philosophizing.

   Two doctors of the schools were philosophizing on the advantages of
   mankind above all other creatures.
